\end_layout

\end_inset

 billion in additional annual consumption.
 Cash users benefit purely because the decline in interchange fees lowers effective prices,
 and they are not hurt by the loss of rewards,
 since they never received them in the first place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even though much of the literature focuses on transfers between card and cash users,
 regulated debit card users also benefit substantially from capping interchange fees.
 For this group,
 average consumer surplus would increase by 
