 shows the results of regressing changes in log sales and changes in log ticket size on the change in average interchange rates paid at restaurants in the 1 year and 2 year windows after the implementation the Durbin Amendment.
 Log ticket size is measured as the log of the ratio of the dollar value of sales to the number of transactions.
 The pre-debit share is the share of debit card transactions at the restaurant from October 2010 to September 2011.
 The Change in Fees is defined as the change in the average per transaction debit interchange fee for a regulated debit card at the store,
 as computed from the average ticket size measured from October 2010 to September 2011 and the public debit interchange schedule prior to the Durbin Amendment.
